        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 6 at 9:27PM EDT by NWS Charleston WV</headline>
        <description>At 926 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
North Bend State Park, or 9 miles west of Harrisville, moving east at
10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Harrisville, North Bend State Park, Ellenboro, Cairo, Smithville,
Freeport, Nutter Farm, Big Springs, Brohard, Macfarlan, and
Petroleum.

This includes Route 50 in West Virginia between mile markers 23 and
37.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
